| Notes                   = * The film was released as part of a double feature entitled ''Hulk Vs'' The other segment is [[Hulk vs. Thor]].
* ''Hulk vs. Wolverine'' is based on {{cl|Incredible Hulk Vol 1 181}}, [[James Howlett (Earth-616)|Wolverine]]'s first appearance.
| Trivia                  = * Despite not possessing any score at Rotten Tomatoes, both segments of the movie was generally well received from the fans.<ref>[https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/hulk_vs Hulk Vs. at Rotten Tomatoes]</ref>
* Screenplay writer Christopher Yost has stated that ''Hulk Vs. Wolverine'' takes place before the events of ''Avengers: Earth's Mightiest Heroes''. {{cite|ref=true|url=https://twitter.com/yost/status/1201368120771792896|title="I’d say before."|work=Twitter|first=Christopher|last=Yost|date=1 December 2019|accessdate=3 December 2019}}
* Years later, it was revealed that the members of Team X who had been inside the facility when it exploded during the climax had all survived.{{cite|ref=true|url=https://twitter.com/yost/status/1356602006916395008|title="They survived.  They always do."|work=Twitter|first=Christopher|last=Yost|date=2 Februrary 2021|accessdate=2 Februrary 2021}}

